# Story Thread Template

## Tweet 1 (Hook)
{Drop the reader into the most dramatic, surprising, or interesting moment of the story. No background first.}

A thread:

## Tweet 2 (Setup)
{Back up and set the scene. Who, when, what was the situation? Keep it tight: 2-3 sentences max.}

## Tweet 3 (Rising Action)
{What happened next? Build tension. Each tweet should make the reader want to see the next one.}

## Tweet 4-N (Conflict / Turning Points)
{The core of the story. What went wrong? What was the challenge? What decision had to be made?}

{Each tweet covers one beat of the story. Use specific details: names, numbers, timestamps, exact quotes.}

<!-- Repeat for as many beats as the story needs. Aim for 3-5 conflict/turning point tweets. -->

## Tweet N+1 (Resolution)
{What happened in the end? Deliver the outcome with specific results.}

## Tweet N+2 (Lesson)
{The takeaway. What did this experience teach? Frame it as something the reader can apply.}

## Final Tweet (CTA)
{Invite engagement: ask the reader if they've had a similar experience, share a related resource, or suggest a next action.}
